dct_title_s: [Amu Darya and Aral Sea diagrams] No. 12. Section of Amu below Kuwan Jerma, 27th. July; No. 13. Section of Amu below Kuwan Jerma, 2nd. Septr.; No. 14. Section of Amu above Kuwan Jerma-Khodjeili, 27th. July; No. 15. Section of Amu above Kuwan Jerma-Khodjeili, 1st. Septr
dct_description_sm: Title given by cataloger. Depth shown by soundings and bathymetric sections. Relief shown by contours, hachures, and spot heights. Scale of diagrams 2-3, 7-8, 10, 12-20 ca. 1:5,690; vertical scale ca. 1:285. Horizontal and vertical scales of diagram 5 ca. 1:1,440. Scale of diagram 9 ca. 1:15,360. Scale of diagram 21 ca. 1:4,528,000. Scale of map ca. 1:2,821,000 at 43° N. From: Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 45 (1875), pp. 367-413; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687.
